  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operation Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities: </strong><br /><br />a) Liaise with Project and Operations Manager for work scheduling and site arrangement.</p><p>b) Assume roles and responsibilities as Project Engineer and/or Coordinator for assigned projects.</p><p>c) Assist Project/Operations Manager in fulfilling project management duties.</p><p>d) Report and support all operational matters, including administration, manpower scheduling, training, staff evaluations, and progress tracking.</p><p>e) Prepare work plans for execution of various project components.</p><p>f) Supervise and manage site activities and provide updates to the Project Manager.</p><p>g) Ensure high quality of work and timely project completion.</p><p>h) Attend project coordination and progress meetings.</p><p>i) Track and update workflow related to purchase order status.</p><p>j) Conduct site surveys and prepare quotations for client submission.</p><p>k) Troubleshoot issues and provide alternative technical solutions to clients, including maintenance support.</p><p>l) Manage and maintain all project-related documentation, such as service reports, maintenance logs, risk assessments, certificates of completion, O&M manuals, and as-built drawings.</p><p>m) Contribute to capability development and business development initiatives.</p><p>n) Implement and uphold Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) policies and requirements.</p><p>o) Educate, interpret, and ensure compliance of WSH standards among site workers.</p><p>p) Conduct site briefings and training for site supervisors.</p><p>q) Evaluate site supervisor and worker performance for continuous improvement.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma or Degree in Facilities Maintenance, Building, Construction Management, or a related field</p><p>•\tHigher NITEC, ITE, or equivalent qualification in a relevant discipline</p><p>•\tRelevant experience in site coordination, engineering, or supervisory roles</p><p>•\tStrong understanding of Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) practices and site operations</p><p>•\tExcellent communication, coordination, and organizational skills</p><p>•\tAbility to work independently and manage multiple tasks</p><p>•\tProficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint)</p>",
